<?php
	include_once 'header.php';
	    
	if (isset($_REQUEST[1])){
		$gui->setTitle ("SYWTBAP: Team Owner");
		
		$gui->addContent('<p>Team Ownership! Some would argue it\'s the most important aspect of Podracing. Then again, some would argue that drinking urine can grant absolution for your previous bad deeds. Take that as you will. At any rate, team ownership is not only important, it\'s crucial. Without team owners, there would be no teams. Without teams, there would be no Podracing. And that would be boring.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>So, the first thing you need to know how to do is start your team! To do this, click on the Options button <img src=images/options_button.jpg> which will take you to the admin section. Then simply click on the Create Team button <img src=images/create.png>.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>This will bring you to a simple form to fill out. If you can\'t figure out the form, I suggest that you don\'t create your own team. Your logo URL, website URL, and slogan are all optional, but I do suggest you at least have a slogan, as it makes you look more attractive as a team looking for members.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Before we go on to team management, I should give you a brief overview of how a team works. Teams are composed of a Team Owner and Team Members. The Owner and Members donate their account credits into the Team Coffers. The Team Coffers are used for everything in Podracer, from registration fees to the actual purchase and modification of pods. This sport gets expensive, so its good to have a big bank roll or a lot of team members so your Team Coffers allow you to purchase items.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>The Team Owner is the only person who can purchase and modify pods, as well as sign them up in races. Additionally, the team member can also remove and promote members, as well as distribute credits to them from the Team Coffers. With that cleared up, lets move on.');
		$gui->addContent('Team Betting is different from Spectator Betting because of the addition of Race Vouchers. When you go to the betting page to place a bet, if you currently have any pods registered in any races, you will be issued a Race Voucher. You will get one Voucher for each pod you have entered in every pending race. Race vouchers are worth 1,000,000 credits for betting purposes!');
		$gui->addContent('<p align="center"><img src=images/manual/voucher.png></p>');
		$gui->addContent('If you click on "Use Voucher" you will follow the normal betting process outlined in the <a href=?1>Spectator</a> section, except that you have a pending 1 million credit line to start with. If you chose to use your voucher without any extra, put 0 in the amount box when picking your pod, and then click submit. The 5 million credit limit is till maintained, so the most you can bet on top of your voucher is 4 million. If you withdraw a voucher bet, 85% of anything above the 1 million voucher credit will be returned to your account. Lets move on.');	
		$gui->addContent('<p>Once you have your team created, return to the admin menu and you will see all the team management resources you could possibly imagine!');
		$gui->addContent('<p align="center"><img src= images/manual/options.png></p>');
		$gui->addContent('<p>I\'ll give you a walkthrough on some of the more complex ones later, and a brief overview of the simpler options now.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Modify button <img src=images/modify_team.png> will allow you to edit your Team Name, Logo URL, Website URL, and Slogan. ');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Members button <img src=images/members.png> will allow you to promote another member to Team Leader and become a regular member of the team as well as deleting members from your team which you no longer want around for any reason.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Click on the eMail button <img src=images/email_team.png> will bring you to a simple form which will allow you to send an eMail to all the members of your team. This is useful for getting information to all your members without needing mailing lists and such.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Distribute button <img src=images/distribute.png> will give you the option of dealing out Team Funds to your Team Members. You select the team member from the dropdown box, enter the amount of credits you want to give them from the general coffers, and submit. Your team funds will be reduced by that amount, and the team members account credits will increase by that amount.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Contribute button <img src=images/contribute.png> will allow you to add credits to the General Coffers. However many credits you enter into the field will be removed from your account balance and added to the Team Coffers. <b>This is the first and most crucial step you should take when starting a team!</b> Team Coffers are used for everything in Podracer, and your individual account balances don\'t matter as far as things within Podracer are concerned.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Team button <img src=images/team.png> will allow you to toggle membership acceptance on and off. If your team is set to accept members, anyone can join your team. If your membership acceptance is off, nobody will be able to join your team. This is useful if you don\'t want new people on your already prime team, or if you need more new blood in the pool.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Withdraw button <img src=images/withdraw.png> will allow you to withdraw your pod from a signed up race. This feature can be done via the Races menu as well. When you withdraw a pod, you get back 75% of your entry fee, and your registrations in the race are destroyed. ');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Disband button <img src=images/disband.png> will allow you to close your team. When you close your team, all your team assets are sold off (pods and modifications) and your liquidated assets are then evenly split between the current members of the team. This is an automatic split, so if you wish to pay back members differently, it is suggested you liquidate your own assets, distribute the credits manually, then disband the team.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Those are the simple functions of team ownership. <a href=?pod>Continue to Pod Purchase/Modification</a>.');
