	} elseif (isset($_REQUEST[pod])){	
		$gui->setTitle ("SYWTBAP: Pod Purchase/Modification");
		
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the Pods button <img src=images/pods.png> will allow you to sell and tweak your pods. However, this will be fairly useless to you at this point, as you don\'t own any pods! So, lets cover buying pods.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>First, you need to have credits in your Team Coffers. If you do, then your ready to buy pods and upgrade them. Click on the Junkyard button <img src=images/junkyard_button.jpg>.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>The first thing you will see in the Junkyard is two main menus. Pod Types and Mod Types. The first thing you need to purchase is a pod, so we\'ll start with Pod Types. ');
		$gui->addContent('<p>The pods are organized into categories which are fairly self explanatory. For this exercise, we\'ll go with a Stats Tradeoff pod. Pods in this category trade certain stats for other (i.e. high control [turning, traction, breaking] and low speed [acceleration, top speed]). The pod we will go with is the Farwan & Glott FG 8T8-Twin Block2 Special.');
		$gui->addContent('<p align="center"><img src=images/manual/pod.png></p>');
		$gui->addContent('<p>This is the pod we\'re looking at buying. This page displays everything you need to know about a pod. ');
		$gui->addContent('<p>The stats of the pod involve how the pod runs on the track. They may seem low when you look at some of the courses, which they are. Most pods need modifications to have any hope of surviving on the track. Given the stats of the pod, I think I have a plan in mind to tune it up into a race winner. So, I\'m going to buy the pod. This is accomplished by clicking on the link below the pod name, [Purchase This Pod]. The pod cost is 2,400,000 and there are an unlimited amount of these pods. Some pods, like special editions, have only a certain amount available, and will no longer be sold after that number reaches zero, so only the fastest will be able to snag these beauties. ');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Once we click the link, we\'ll be asked for our pod name. This is where you enter the name for your craft (which can be changed later). Once you have entered a name, submit the form. If you have enough credits in your Team Coffers to cover the cost of the pod, you\'ll be the owner of a brand-new Podracer! Congratulations!');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Now that you own your first pod, you will need to modify it. For this, click the Junkyard button in the menu again, and return to the Junkyard Menu.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Now we will look at Modifications. Modifications, like pods, are broken down into categories. They are also fairly self explanatory. The only thing you need to know about modifications is that you can only install one modification "type" on a single pod. That means you can only install one part from the Acceleration category on a pod, along with one part from the Top Speed category, one from the Stability Upgrades and so forth.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>When browsing modifications, pay attention to the printout of their stats next to their name. For example, the Intake/Output Tuner (Traction -2, Turning -2, Acceleration +3, Top speed +3, Air brake -2, Repair +1), when installed on your pod, will do the following:');
