		$gui->addContent('<p>If you click on the name of your pod, you will be able to view the current stats of your pod. If you click on Tweak, you will be brought to the Tweak menu, which will be covered soon. If you click on Edit, you will be able to change your pod\'s name and owner (should you trade it to another team and need to transfer it). If you click on Sell, you will sell your pod, along with all modifications, for 75% of the market value of both the pod and the modifications. These credits will be added back into the Team Coffers.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Clicking on the name of one of the modifications listed below your pod will show you the information on the modification. If you click on the [Remove] link next to a modification, you will resell that modification to the junkyard for 75% of its market value.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>With that covered, we will move on to tweaks. Tweaks are small changes to your pod (adding engine wings, rewiring the controls, installing better cooling systems etc) that change the stats of your pod. Tweaks are free, and you may set and delete as many tweaks as you want for no cost as often as you want.');
		$gui->addContent('<p align="center"><img src= images/manual/tweak.png></p>');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Next to the name of each tweak is a dropdown box. From this box, you can select if you want to install the tweak, and, if applicable, what level of the tweak you wish to install. Next to the tweak level, you will see some stats along with +s and -s. Anything listed as +<stat> will slightly increase that stat, and anything listed as -<stat> will slightly reduce that stat.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Depending on what kind of stats you want to change will determine what tweaks you want to activate. The stats which they modify are shorthand of their actual value names. The list is:');
		$gui->addContent('<br />Tr = Traction');
		$gui->addContent('<br />Tu = Turning');
		$gui->addContent('<br />Sp = Top Speed');
		$gui->addContent('<br />Ac = Acceleration');
		$gui->addContent('<br />Co = Cooling');
		$gui->addContent('<br />Re = Repair');
		$gui->addContent('<p>Once you\'ve run through your tweak menu, submit the changes, and your pod will be successfully tweaked.');
		$gui->addContent('<p>That\'s all there is to know about pods! <a href=?race>Continue to Race Registration</a>.');
